description:
&lt;p&gt;East Cheshire NHS Trust is looking to recruit Bank Doctors to enhance our already successful Medical Staff Bank. Applications are welcomed from doctors to work on an ad-hoc basis in the following specialties to help provide consistent, high level patient care and to assist with the continuity of care that the Trust provides.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Anaesthetics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology (Middle Grade only)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Paediatrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Orthopaedics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this is ‘Bank’ work, it is on an ‘as and when’ basis with no guaranteed hours, however it does offer doctors increased flexibility by selecting shifts to work around their lifestyle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working patterns vary from booking to booking and can include weekday day duty, evening, weekend and night duty on full shift and on-call rotas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note, you must have a minimum of 6 months NHS/UK experience in order to proceed with joining our Bank. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bank rates are subject to change (hourly rate inclusive of 12.5% annual leave payment)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FY1 £40.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FY2 £50.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IMT/ST1/2 £60.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ST3+ £70.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specialty Doctor £70.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consultant £90.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Doctors joining the Trust Medical Bank will be expected to complete pre-employment checks inclusive of GMC registration, satisfactory references, health clearance, enhanced DBS check identity and right to work checks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to the terms of a Bank contract, we are unable to meet the criteria for Tier 2 sponsorship for visa purposes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is for Bank hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 30th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/p&gt;
